org.baswell.sessioncookie

Interface SessionCookieParameters

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    SessionCookieDefaultParameters

    public interface SessionCookieParameters
    All parameters used by SessionCookie. These parameters are not cached and will be called on HTTP request threads. It's important that each of these methods return immediately (no IO blocking) or request performance will be impacted.

      • getSessionTimeoutMinutes

        default int getSessionTimeoutMinutes()
        The time, in minutes, from creation time that sessions are allowed to remain active. A negative time indicates the session should never timeout.
        Returns:
        DEFAULT_SESSION_TIMEOUT_MINUTES by default

      • getInactivityTimeoutSeconds

        default int getInactivityTimeoutSeconds()

      • getMaxInMemorySessions

        default int getMaxInMemorySessions()
        The maximum number of sessions that are cached in memory. A zero or negative value indicates that no sessions are cached.

        DEFAULT_MAX_IN_MEMORY_SESSIONS by default

      • getPurgeSessionCacheWithBackgroundThread

        default boolean getPurgeSessionCacheWithBackgroundThread()
        Indicates if a background thread should be used to removed candidates from the session cache. If false sessions will be removed from the cache on request threads.
        Returns:
        DEFAULT_PURGE_SESSION_CACHE_WITH_BACKGROUND_THREAD by default
